{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"sourceId":"pirkeiAvot","displayName":"Pirkei Avot (Ethics of the Fathers)","type":"scripture","language":"English","edition":"Public Domain Translation","primaryCategory":"Faith & Devotion","subcategory":"Jewish","audienceTags":["ethics","wisdom"],"sortPriority":35,"itemCount":41,"supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true,"browseOrder":"chapterVerse","groupingLevels":["chapter","mishna"],"groupingLabels":["Chapter","Mishna"],"dataPath":"Data/Collections/PirkeiAvot_English.json","version":"1.0"},"data":[{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-1","text":"Moses received the Torah from Sinai and transmitted it to Joshua, Joshua to the Elders, the Elders to the Prophets, and the Prophets transmitted it to the Men of the Great Assembly. They said three things: Be patient in judgment, raise up many disciples, and make a fence for the Torah.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:1","chapter":1,"verse":1,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"1"},"sequenceIndex":0},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-2","text":"Shimon the Righteous was one of the last of the Great Assembly. He would say: The world stands on three things — on Torah, on service of God, and on deeds of lovingkindness.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:2","chapter":1,"verse":2,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"2"},"sequenceIndex":1},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-3","text":"Antigonus of Socho received the tradition from Shimon the Righteous. He would say: Do not be as servants who serve the master for the sake of receiving a reward. Rather, be as servants who serve the master not for the sake of receiving a reward. And let the fear of Heaven be upon you.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:3","chapter":1,"verse":3,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"3"},"sequenceIndex":2},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-4","text":"Yosi ben Yoezer of Tzreidah and Yosi ben Yochanan of Jerusalem received the tradition from them. Yosi ben Yoezer would say: Let your home be a meeting place for the wise. Sit in the dust of their feet, and drink their words with thirst.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:4","chapter":1,"verse":4,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"4"},"sequenceIndex":3},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-5","text":"Yosi ben Yochanan of Jerusalem would say: Let your home be wide open, and let the poor be members of your household.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:5","chapter":1,"verse":5,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"5"},"sequenceIndex":4},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-6","text":"Joshua ben Perachia and Nitai the Arbelite received from them. Joshua ben Perachia would say: Acquire a teacher for yourself, buy yourself a friend, and judge every person to the side of merit.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:6","chapter":1,"verse":6,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"6"},"sequenceIndex":5},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-7","text":"Nitai the Arbelite would say: Distance yourself from a bad neighbor, do not bond with a wicked person, and do not despair of retribution.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:7","chapter":1,"verse":7,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"7"},"sequenceIndex":6},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-8","text":"Judah ben Tabbai and Shimon ben Shetach received from them. Judah ben Tabbai would say: Do not act as a counselor to judges. When the litigants stand before you, consider them both as guilty; and when they are dismissed from before you, consider them both as innocent.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:8","chapter":1,"verse":8,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"8"},"sequenceIndex":7},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-9","text":"Shimon ben Shetach would say: Thoroughly interrogate the witnesses. Be careful with your words, lest from them they learn to lie.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:9","chapter":1,"verse":9,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"9"},"sequenceIndex":8},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-10","text":"Shemayah and Avtalyon received from them. Shemayah would say: Love work, loathe mastery over others, and avoid intimacy with the government.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:10","chapter":1,"verse":10,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"10"},"sequenceIndex":9},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-11","text":"Avtalyon would say: Scholars, be careful with your words. For you may be exiled to a place of evil waters, and the disciples who come after you may drink and die, and the Name of Heaven will be desecrated.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:11","chapter":1,"verse":11,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"11"},"sequenceIndex":10},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-12","text":"Hillel and Shammai received from them. Hillel would say: Be among the disciples of Aaron — love peace, pursue peace, love people, and bring them closer to Torah.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:12","chapter":1,"verse":12,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"12"},"sequenceIndex":11},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-13","text":"He would also say: A name made great is a name destroyed. He who does not increase, decreases. He who does not learn deserves to die. And one who makes use of the crown shall pass away.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:13","chapter":1,"verse":13,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"13"},"sequenceIndex":12},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-14","text":"He would also say: If I am not for myself, who is for me? And if I am only for myself, what am I? And if not now, when?","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:14","chapter":1,"verse":14,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"14"},"sequenceIndex":13},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-15","text":"Shammai would say: Make your Torah study a fixed practice. Say little and do much. And receive every person with a pleasant countenance.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:15","chapter":1,"verse":15,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"15"},"sequenceIndex":14},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-16","text":"Rabban Gamliel would say: Provide yourself with a teacher, and remove yourself from doubt; and do not accustom yourself to tithe by estimation.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:16","chapter":1,"verse":16,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"16"},"sequenceIndex":15},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-17","text":"His son Shimon would say: All my life I grew up among the Sages, and I found nothing better for a person than silence. Study is not the most important thing, but action. And all who talk excessively bring sin.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:17","chapter":1,"verse":17,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"17"},"sequenceIndex":16},{"id":"pirkei-avot-1-18","text":"Rabban Shimon ben Gamliel would say: The world stands on three things — on truth, on justice, and on peace.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 1:18","chapter":1,"verse":18,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"1","mishna":"18"},"sequenceIndex":17},{"id":"pirkei-avot-2-1","text":"Rabbi would say: Which is the right path for man to choose for himself? Whatever is harmonious for the one who does it, and harmonious for mankind.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 2:1","chapter":2,"verse":1,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","mishna":"1"},"sequenceIndex":18},{"id":"pirkei-avot-2-2","text":"Rabban Gamliel the son of Rabbi Judah HaNassi would say: Torah study is good together with a worldly occupation, for the toil of them both causes sin to be forgotten. All Torah study that is not accompanied by work will ultimately cease and lead to sin.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 2:2","chapter":2,"verse":2,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","mishna":"2"},"sequenceIndex":19},{"id":"pirkei-avot-2-3","text":"Be careful about the government, for they befriend a person only for their own needs. They appear to be friends when it is beneficial to them, but they do not stand by a person at the time of his distress.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 2:3","chapter":2,"verse":3,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","mishna":"3"},"sequenceIndex":20},{"id":"pirkei-avot-2-4","text":"Hillel would say: Do not trust in yourself until the day of your death. Do not judge your fellow until you have reached his place.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 2:4","chapter":2,"verse":4,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","mishna":"4"},"sequenceIndex":21},{"id":"pirkei-avot-2-5","text":"He would also say: A boor cannot be sin-fearing, and an ignoramus cannot be pious; a bashful one cannot learn, and an impatient one cannot teach; one who is excessively occupied in business cannot become a sage. In a place where there are no men, strive to be a man.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 2:5","chapter":2,"verse":5,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","mishna":"5"},"sequenceIndex":22},{"id":"pirkei-avot-2-6","text":"He also saw a skull floating upon the water and said to it: Because you drowned others, you were drowned; and those who drowned you, will themselves be drowned.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 2:6","chapter":2,"verse":6,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","mishna":"6"},"sequenceIndex":23},{"id":"pirkei-avot-2-7","text":"He would also say: One who increases flesh, increases worms. One who increases money, increases worry. One who increases property, increases theft. One who increases wives, increases witchcraft. One who increases maidservants, increases promiscuity. One who increases man-servants, increases theft. But one who increases Torah, increases life.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 2:7","chapter":2,"verse":7,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","mishna":"7"},"sequenceIndex":24},{"id":"pirkei-avot-2-8","text":"He would also say: Who is wise? One who learns from every man. Who is mighty? One who conquers his inclination. Who is rich? One who is satisfied with his lot. Who is honored? One who honors others.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 2:8","chapter":2,"verse":8,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","mishna":"8"},"sequenceIndex":25},{"id":"pirkei-avot-2-9","text":"He would also say: If I am not for myself, who is for me? If I am for myself alone, what am I? And if not now, when?","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 2:9","chapter":2,"verse":9,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","mishna":"9"},"sequenceIndex":26},{"id":"pirkei-avot-2-10","text":"Rabban Yochanan ben Zakkai received the tradition from Hillel and Shammai. He used to say: If you have learned much Torah, do not congratulate yourself, for that is what you were created to do.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 2:10","chapter":2,"verse":10,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"2","mishna":"10"},"sequenceIndex":27},{"id":"pirkei-avot-3-1","text":"Akavia the son of Mehalalel would say: Reflect upon three things and you will not come to sin: Know from where you came, where you are going, and before Whom you will give account and reckoning.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 3:1","chapter":3,"verse":1,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"3","mishna":"1"},"sequenceIndex":28},{"id":"pirkei-avot-3-2","text":"Rabbi Chanina, the deputy High Priest, would say: Pray for the welfare of the government, for if not for the fear of it, a man would swallow his fellow alive.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 3:2","chapter":3,"verse":2,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"3","mishna":"2"},"sequenceIndex":29},{"id":"pirkei-avot-3-14","text":"He would also say: Beloved is man, for he was created in the image of God. It is an even greater love that it was made known to him that he was created in the image of God.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 3:14","chapter":3,"verse":14,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"3","mishna":"14"},"sequenceIndex":30},{"id":"pirkei-avot-3-18","text":"Rabbi Elazar HaKappar would say: Jealousy, lust and honor remove a person from the world.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 3:18","chapter":3,"verse":18,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"3","mishna":"18"},"sequenceIndex":31},{"id":"pirkei-avot-4-1","text":"Ben Zoma would say: Who is wise? One who learns from every man. Who is mighty? One who conquers his inclination. Who is rich? One who is satisfied with his lot. Who is honored? One who honors others.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 4:1","chapter":4,"verse":1,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"4","mishna":"1"},"sequenceIndex":32},{"id":"pirkei-avot-4-2","text":"Ben Azzai would say: Run to pursue a minor mitzvah, and flee from sin. For one mitzvah leads to another mitzvah, and one sin leads to another sin; for the reward of a mitzvah is a mitzvah, and the reward of a sin is a sin.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 4:2","chapter":4,"verse":2,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"4","mishna":"2"},"sequenceIndex":33},{"id":"pirkei-avot-4-15","text":"Rabbi Eliezer HaKappar would say: Jealousy, lust and honor remove a person from the world.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 4:15","chapter":4,"verse":15,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"4","mishna":"15"},"sequenceIndex":34},{"id":"pirkei-avot-4-16","text":"Rabbi Yaakov would say: This world is like a lobby before the World to Come. Prepare yourself in the lobby so that you may enter the banquet hall.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 4:16","chapter":4,"verse":16,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"4","mishna":"16"},"sequenceIndex":35},{"id":"pirkei-avot-5-1","text":"With ten utterances the world was created. What does this come to teach us? Could it not have been created with one utterance? This is to make the wicked accountable for destroying a world that was created with ten utterances, and to reward the righteous for sustaining a world that was created with ten utterances.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 5:1","chapter":5,"verse":1,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"5","mishna":"1"},"sequenceIndex":36},{"id":"pirkei-avot-5-22","text":"Yehuda ben Tema would say: Be bold as a leopard, light as an eagle, swift as a deer, and strong as a lion, to do the will of your Father in Heaven.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 5:22","chapter":5,"verse":22,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"5","mishna":"22"},"sequenceIndex":37},{"id":"pirkei-avot-5-23","text":"He would also say: At five years of age, the study of Scripture. At ten, the study of Mishnah. At thirteen, the obligation to observe the commandments. At fifteen, the study of Talmud. At eighteen, marriage. At twenty, pursuit of livelihood. At thirty, strength. At forty, wisdom. At fifty, able to give counsel. At sixty, old age. At seventy, ripe old age. At eighty, remarkable strength. At ninety, stooped. At one hundred, it is as if he has died and passed from the world.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 5:23","chapter":5,"verse":23,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"5","mishna":"23"},"sequenceIndex":38},{"id":"pirkei-avot-6-1","text":"The Sages taught in the language of the Mishnah — and their memory is for a blessing: One who learns Torah for its own sake merits many things.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 6:1","chapter":6,"verse":1,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"6","mishna":"1"},"sequenceIndex":39},{"id":"pirkei-avot-6-6","text":"Torah is greater than the priesthood and kingship, for kingship is acquired with thirty virtues, the priesthood with twenty-four, but the Torah with forty-eight things.","author":"Pirkei Avot","source":"Pirkei Avot 6:6","chapter":6,"verse":6,"tags":["scripture","judaism","wisdom","language:english","collection:pirkeiavot"],"groups":{"chapter":"6","mishna":"6"},"sequenceIndex":40}]}